WEBVTT

00:08.742 --> 00:10.266
Sorry I'm late,

00:10.343 --> 00:12.277
but I have a very good excuse.

00:12.345 --> 00:13.676
Picture this:

00:13.747 --> 00:15.840
I'm just getting ready
to leave the Mess Hall

00:15.915 --> 00:18.179
when Ensign Wildman
goes into labor.

00:18.251 --> 00:20.879
What else could I do
but deliver the baby?

00:20.954 --> 00:22.546
Oh, you should
have been there, Harry.

00:22.622 --> 00:25.853
There is nothing like bringing
a new life into the world.

00:25.925 --> 00:27.586
I think I missed my calling.

00:29.863 --> 00:30.989
What if I told you

00:31.064 --> 00:33.294
the turbolift got stuck
on Deck 6?

00:33.366 --> 00:35.197
This is the third time
you've been late this week,

00:35.268 --> 00:36.292
Mr. Paris.

00:36.369 --> 00:38.462
It won't happen again.

00:38.538 --> 00:41.473
Commander, I am picking up
a distress call

00:41.541 --> 00:43.008
on one of the upper
subspace bands.

00:43.143 --> 00:44.337
What's the source?

00:44.411 --> 00:45.844
A small spacecraft.

00:45.912 --> 00:47.243
No weapon systems.

00:47.313 --> 00:48.905
One life-form aboard.

00:48.982 --> 00:50.609
Extremely weak life signs.

00:50.683 --> 00:51.911
Slow to half impulse.

00:51.985 --> 00:54.783
According to the bioscanner,
it's a Vidiian female.

00:54.854 --> 00:56.549
Open a channel.

00:56.623 --> 00:58.181
No response.

00:58.258 --> 00:59.589
She may be too sick.

01:00.760 --> 01:02.660
Or maybe
it's some kind of trick.

01:02.729 --> 01:05.630
Preliminary scans show no other
Vidiian ships in this sector.

01:05.698 --> 01:07.598
It is unlikely
that this is a trap.

01:07.667 --> 01:09.328
Commander Chakotay,
notify the Doctor.

01:09.402 --> 01:11.267
Mr. Kim, beam the woman
to Sick Bay.

01:11.337 --> 01:12.463
Aye, Captain.

